@{b}Ucode Glyph Packs@{ub}

There is only a basic set of glyph files included with my Ucode release.
These must be supplemented by downloading @{b}"Ucode Glyph Packs"@{ub} which will
progressively appear on the Aminet as they are ready.@{ub}


@{b}Only a Pre-Release..@{ub}


This is only a PRE-RELEASE of my Unicode package - please email me if
you are interested in receiving updates.

Also, if you are interested in adding to the suite of glyph files, or in
helping with the project in other ways, please let me know so we can work
cooperatively.

I would be especially delighted if people could make non-English
translations of UCODE:Catalogs files, and/or this guide. I will soon bring
out a Unicode text editor to facilitate this.

I feel like a hypocrite for only having Ucode in English, but although I
can understand several modern languages, especially French, my knowledge is
not good enough to make my own translation. Sorry about that.

@endnode

